Package: voxfree
Version: 0.1.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: VoxFree Project <voxfree@example.com>
Installed-Size: 200
Depends: bash (>= 5.0), wl-clipboard, alsa-utils, libnotify-bin, wev, python3-venv, ffmpeg, sox, libsox-fmt-all, python3-gi, gir1.2-ayatanaappindicator3-0.1
Recommends: xdotool, ydotool, speech-dispatcher
Suggests: mycroft-mimic3-tts
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/owaisforandroid/VoxFree
Description: Offline voice tools for Ubuntu 24.04 GNOME/Wayland
 VoxFree provides two offline voice features for the GNOME desktop:
 .
  * ReadLoud (TTS): Highlight any text and press F9 to hear it read
    aloud using Mycroft Mimic 3 neural text-to-speech. Press F9 again
    to stop. Change voice with: voxfree --voice
 .
  * SpeakToType (STT): Press F10 to start recording, speak, press F11
    to stop. Your words are transcribed by OpenAI Whisper (base.en,
    offline, ~2s) and pasted at the cursor via ydotool.
 .
 All processing is local. No cloud APIs, no internet required after
 initial setup. Works on Ubuntu 24.04 with GNOME on Wayland.
 .
 Note: mycroft-mimic3-tts is not in Ubuntu repositories. Install it
 separately from https://github.com/MycroftAI/mimic3/releases or run
 'sudo voxfree --install' after installation.
